wikipedia_page.main: Rosetta Phoebe "Binky" Blair-White (10 September 1894 – 6 March 1991) was an Irish tennis player.

response: In 1918, he married Irish tennis player Phoebe Blair-White. In the 1960s, they moved to Lifford, County Donegal, and later, they lived in Strabane County Tyrone. He is buried in Lifford, County Donegal beside his wife.

She qualified for the 1924 Summer Olympics in Paris, France. She would play in the women's singles event and would compete in the first round against Phoebe Blair-White; but she withdrawn. She also withdrawn for the mixed doubles event where she would play with partner Camille Wolff.
